cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.AI

The paper deals with routing in Delay Tolerant Networks (DTNs), which is a subfield of computer networking. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also involves the use of high-dimensional Euclidean space, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper uses probability distributions to represent node mobility, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
